headline: Visa price target raised to $347 from $324 at Goldman Sachs
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Will Nance raised the firm’s price target on Visa (V) to $347 from $324 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. Since the election, the median payment technology stock in coverage has increased 18%, with higher beta growth names with pro-cyclical exposure, among other factors, outperforming the most, the analyst tells investors in a research note. The firm believes fintech is a net beneficiary of a stronger economy and inflation as well as many of the potential policy changes
